<item>
            <title>[LU-17089] Bug in the barrier code could cause barrier freeze to fail everytime</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17089</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The barrier code has a bug that could cause the freeze to fail everytime. barrier freeze would be called before trying a FS backup, but would repeatedly fail due to an issue in the mdd_trans_create() function.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://git.whamcloud.com/?p=fs/lustre-release.git;a=blob;f=lustre/mdd/mdd_trans.c;hb=2b0a71081d9c2465cb4b6368fede266fcde91b82#l49&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git.whamcloud.com/?p=fs/lustre-release.git;a=blob;f=lustre/mdd/mdd_trans.c;hb=2b0a71081d9c2465cb4b6368fede266fcde91b82#l49&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The barrier entry increments the global counter barrier_writer, but it does not get decremented if mdd_child_ops() returns error. If the barrier_writer counter does not go to 0, the freeze cannot happen.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
